Hey all,

Today, we encountered an issue where it seems that our WPILib VS Code is messed up?? I won’t allow us to create any new classes/commands, or really any other things like that specific to WPILib. Also the layout of everything has changed, along with the addition of new files(JRE System Library [JavaSE 17], and Project & External Dependencies). Does anyone have any recommendations on how to fix this??

This issue still occurs, even when creating a new project.

The tree you have open under explorer is the “Java Projects” tree, which is why it’s showing the JavaSE 17 and Project & External Dependencies lines and not giving you the same popup dialog options. If you go to the three dots next to “Explorer” it should give you an option to see a Folders view which is the more typical one with a heading of the project folder name.
